[MK] cases #19CF426, #20CM5, #22CF171 called at 9:14am 
Defendant Alan L Schade in court, in custody, with Attorney Karl Huebner. ADA Michael Witt in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
ADA Witt verifies victim rights compliance. 

In Case #22CF171 Initial Appearance is completed and Preliminary Hearing is held: 
--Service of the Complaint is admitted; reading is waived; the charges and maximum penalties are recited. 
--After Mr. Schade indicates that he does not understand the Repeater allegation, the Court and parties discuss the requirements. 
--The parties indicate that the existence of the bonds at the time of the offenses is not in dispute, in relation to the Bailjumping charges. The subject bonds were a single bond in Jefferson County cases 19CF426 and 20CM5, a bond that was in Columbia County case 21CF528, and a bond Waukesha County cases #21CF616 and #21CM749; and these were in effect on the subject date of violation.
--Det. A. Kleist- sworn and testifies
---direct examination by ADA Witt
---cross examination by Attorney Huebner
--Arguments are given by counsel.
--The Court finds probable cause that Mr. Schade committed a felony. The Court binds him over for Trial.
--ADA Witt requests that arraignment be scheduled on a later date.
recess 9:53am

Initial appearance on May 6, 2022 at 01:45 pm.

[MK] cases #19CF426, #20CM5, #22CF171 called at 3:30pm 
Defendant Alan L Schade appears by videoconferencing from the Dodge County Jail, in custody.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
The Court finds that the video-connection is sight and sound sufficient.  
ADA Teuber verifies victim rights compliance.  
The Court notes that Mr. Schade has been found eligible for PD representation in the two older cases, however there is no such indication in the new case #22CF171.  The Court directs that the Public Defenders Office continue efforts to appoint counsel for Mr. Schade.
Mr. Schade confirms that he continues to request representation by counsel.
____________
As to Case #22CF171 only:    
The Court does not proceed with the Initial Appearance in the case because Mr. Schade has indicated he wishes to be represented by counsel.  
ADA Teuber requests that the Court establish bond in the new case #22CF171; the State is seeking a $250,000 Cash Bond with conditions.
The Court requires a $250,000 Cash Bond with conditions:  
--no presence at the Ixonia State Bank located in the Town of Ixonia 
--no possession of any weapons
--no acts or threats of violence 
Mr. Schade raises questions regarding the preliminary hearing and the ten day time limit. The Court discusses with Mr. Schade that because he does not have counsel, the Court is setting the case next for a status-of-counsel hearing. Thereafter Mr. Schade requests scheduling of the next hearing on a date soon in time. 
recess 3:38pm 

NEXT:  (1) clerk- please email the Jefferson PD to notify them that Mr. Schade is requesting PD appointment of counsel in Case #22CF171,  (2) Status Conference (status-of-counsel hearing) on all three cases, and Initial Appearance in Case #22CF171--all on May 6th at 1:45pm, (3) the June 7th FSSC and the June 13th Jury Trial dates remain on the Court's calendar in Cases #19CF426 and #20CM5
